{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 9, this is a 5-classification problem.",
    "All the output layer vectors (left column) are given a number (right column) within (0, 1) after Softmax, where the probability of the second row is 0.90, indicating that the classification task belongs to the second category.",
    "SoftMax is formulated as follows:",
    "In contrast to the standard max function, which only returns the maximum value, Softmax ensures that smaller values have smaller probabilities and are not discarded outright.",
    "The denominator of the Softmax function combines all the factors of the original output value, which means that the various probabilities obtained by the Softmax function are correlated with each other."
  ]
}